---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — Amplified Event Strategy"
  description="Privacy policy for Amplified Event Strategy."
  bodyClass="inner-page">

  <div class="container-fluid privacy-section">
    <div class="privacy-inner">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="privacy-updated">Last updated: March 2026</p>

      <h2>Who We Are</h2>
      <p>Amplified Event Strategy is a full-service crypto events agency based in New York, USA. Our website is <a href="https://www.amplifiedeventstrategy.com">www.amplifiedeventstrategy.com</a>. References to "we," "us," or "our" refer to Amplified Event Strategy.</p>
      <p>If you have any questions about this policy, contact us at <a href="mailto:hello@amplifiedeventstrategy.com">hello@amplifiedeventstrategy.com</a>.</p>

      <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
      <p>We may collect the following types of information:</p>
      <p><strong>Information you provide directly:</strong> When you contact us via email or any contact form, we collect your name, email address, and the contents of your message.</p>
      <p><strong>Usage data:</strong> When you visit our website, we may automatically collect information about your device, browser type, operating system, referring URLs, pages visited, and time spent on those pages. This data is collected through analytics tools described below.</p>
      <p><strong>Cookies and tracking technologies:</strong> We use cookies and similar tracking technologies to understand how visitors use our website and to improve your experience. See the Cookies section below for more detail.</p>

      <h2>Cookies</h2>
      <p>Cookies are small text files stored on your device when you visit a website. We use the following types of cookies:</p>
      <p><strong>Essential cookies:</strong> Necessary for the website to function correctly. These cannot be disabled.</p>
      <p><strong>Analytics cookies:</strong> We use analytics tools (such as Google Analytics) to collect anonymous data about how visitors interact with our site — including pages visited, session duration, and traffic sources. This helps us understand what content is useful and improve the site over time. This data is aggregated and does not identify you personally.</p>
      <p><strong>Preference cookies:</strong> These remember choices you make on the site to provide a more personalized experience.</p>
      <p>You can control or disable cookies through your browser settings at any time. Note that disabling certain cookies may affect the functionality of the site.</p>

      <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
      <p>We use the information we collect to:</p>
      <p>— Respond to inquiries and communicate with potential clients</p>
      <p>— Understand how our website is used and improve its performance</p>
      <p>— Monitor and analyze traffic and usage trends</p>
      <p>— Comply with legal obligations</p>
      <p>We do not sell your personal information. We do not use your data for automated decision-making or profiling.</p>

      <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p>We use a number of third-party services that may process your data on our behalf:</p>
      <p><strong>Netlify:</strong> This website is hosted on Netlify, which may log IP addresses and request data at the infrastructure level. See <a href="https://www.netlify.com/privacy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Netlify's privacy policy</a>.</p>
      <p><strong>Google Analytics:</strong> We may use Google Analytics to collect anonymous usage data. Google may transfer this data to servers in the United States or other countries. See <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google's privacy policy</a>.</p>
      <p><strong>Social media platforms:</strong> Our website contains links to Instagram, X (Twitter), LinkedIn, Telegram, and YouTube. If you follow these links, those platforms' own privacy policies will apply.</p>
      <p><strong>Email providers:</strong> Emails sent to us are processed through our email service provider. We do not store your email data beyond what is necessary to respond to your inquiry.</p>

      <h2>Data Retention</h2>
      <p>We retain personal information only for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes for which it was collected, or as required by law. Email correspondence is retained for up to 3 years. Analytics data is retained in accordance with the settings of the analytics platform in use.</p>

      <h2>Data Security</h2>
      <p>We take reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, loss, or disclosure. However, no method of transmission over the internet is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.</p>

      <h2>Your Rights</h2>
      <p>Depending on your location, you may have the following rights regarding your personal data:</p>
      <p>— <strong>Access:</strong> Request a copy of the personal data we hold about you</p>
      <p>— <strong>Correction:</strong> Request correction of inaccurate or incomplete data</p>
      <p>— <strong>Deletion:</strong> Request that we delete your personal data</p>
      <p>— <strong>Objection:</strong> Object to the processing of your data for certain purposes</p>
      <p>— <strong>Portability:</strong> Request your data in a portable, machine-readable format</p>
      <p>To exercise any of these rights, contact us at <a href="mailto:hello@amplifiedeventstrategy.com">hello@amplifiedeventstrategy.com</a>. We will respond within 30 days.</p>

      <h2>California Residents (CCPA)</h2>
      <p>If you are a California resident, you have additional rights under the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA), including the right to know what personal information is collected, the right to delete it, and the right to opt out of the sale of personal information. We do not sell personal information. To make a request, contact us at the email above.</p>

      <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p>Our website is not directed at children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If you believe a child has provided us with personal information, please contact us and we will delete it promptly.</p>

      <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>We may update this privacy policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or legal requirements. Any updates will be posted on this page with a revised date. We encourage you to review this policy periodically.</p>

      <h2>Contact Us</h2>
      <p>If you have any questions, concerns, or requests regarding this privacy policy or how we handle your data, please contact us at:</p>
      <p><strong>Amplified Event Strategy</strong><br />
      New York, USA<br />
      <a href="mailto:hello@amplifiedeventstrategy.com">hello@amplifiedeventstrategy.com</a></p>
    </div>
  </div>

</BaseLayout>
